Btw bruv u just write random words and midjourney makes these 😩😭what I’m saying is this took nooooo skill or work lol

These was like “redhead laying in a shell on a busy street fashion photography 90s cinematic Annie lebowitz” basically tumblr tags that’s it that’s all 😭😭😭

My current feeling is AI is cool but I think it makes everything arbitrary and amplifies the thought WHY MAKE SOMETHING? Lol 
It’s deffo fun and useful, and makes me question is the final product whats important or is knowing the lengths someone went through to make something more important? You could use the prompted image as inspo to then make manually - but if it already looks cool what’s the point in doing that? Maybe it means we will make much more nuanced fantasy art? Or more primitive photography - like is wet plate photography suddenly gonna pop off?
